Paper: hep-th/9511034

Date: 1995-11-06

Title: Mode dependent field renormalization and triviality

Comments: 14 pages, no figures, TeX file

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B367 (1996) 249-253

We critically analyze the introduction of an independent zero momentum modefield renormalization for Phi4. It leads to an infrared divergent effectiveparticles in the broken phase in the continuum limit. It leads to an effectivepotential which is not the low energy limit of the effective action.